{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"13c99c04-847c-4127-be2c-ba3d9d0fadd6","content":"The template is **functional but not fully publish-ready**. Here's what I found:\n\n**✅ Present & correct:**\n- `identity`, `name`, `shortName`, `author`, `sourceName`\n- `classifications`, `tags` (language + type)\n- `symbols` with a valid `Framework` choice parameter\n\n**⚠️ Missing / recommended for NuGet publishing:**\n\n| Field | Why |\n|---|---|\n| `$schema` | Enables validation — use `\"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"` |\n| `description` | Shown in `dotnet new search` and NuGet.org — critical for discoverability |\n| `groupIdentity` | Groups related templates (e.g. `MyCompany.WebApi`) — expected for NuGet packages |\n| `preferNameDirectory` | Typically `true` for project templates so `dotnet new mywebapi -n Foo` creates a `Foo/` directory |\n\n**💡 Also verify** that you have a `.csproj` or `.nuspec` with `<PackageType>Template</PackageType>` — the template engine requires this for `dotnet new install` from NuGet to work.\n\nIn short: add `$schema`, `description`, `groupIdentity`, and `preferNameDirectory`, and confirm your packaging metadata before publishing.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"dd996161-6ca5-4dc7-be34-aad7854ad7b6","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Let me review this template.json for NuGet publishing readiness. I'll check for required and recommended fields.\n\nRequired fields for a dotnet template:\n- `$schema` - recommended for validation\n- `author` ✓\n- `classifications` ✓\n- `identity` ✓\n- `name` ✓\n- `shortName` ✓\n- `tags` ✓ (language and type)\n- `sourceName` ✓\n\nMissing/issues:\n1. **`$schema`** - Missing. Should be `\"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"` for validation support.\n\n\n2. **`groupIdentity`** - Recommended for NuGet publishing to group related templates.\n3. **`precedence`** - Useful when multiple versions of the same template exist.\n4. **`preferNameDirectory`** - Common to set to `true`.\n5. The `defaultValue` for Framework is `net9.0` which is fine.\n6. No `description` field - this is not strictly required but highly recommended.\n7. The `sourceName` is set which is good for name replacement.\n\nSo the main gaps are the missing `$schema` reference, no `description` field for better discoverability, and the `groupIdentity` and `preferNameDirectory` fields that would polish this up for a NuGet release. It's definitely functional as-is, but adding those would make it more complete.","outputTokens":702,"requestId":"33DF:2310B5:1FD0BB9:23A90AF:69E81B4E"},"id":"cb2002b3-5760-4d27-99fe-46f2d82dca6d","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:50:37.376Z","parentId":"20e15e17-9e4d-4007-b8c4-6328e4cac890"}
